description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you energised by connecting with others? Can you inspire and motivate in challenging circumstances? Do you wanted to join an exciting, dynamic team?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A rare opportunity has arisen for a Band 5 Employment Specialist to join the CNTW Individual Placement and Support service (IPS) providing specialist employment support to people receiving care and treatment from secondary care mental health services across Cumbria, Northumberland, Tyne and Wear.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We’ve supported dozens and dozens of service users secure paid employment that has helped them thrive! We’re fantastic to work for and can guarantee an exciting and varied role that rewards creativity and an action-orientated attitude. We’re keen to add to our dream team and are searching for candidates with values that mirror our own.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Do you think you have what it takes? To discuss the role or find out more please get in touch, either by emailing us at ips@cntw.nhs.uk or searching for team members on LinkedIn for further information about the role and first-hand accounts of why we&#39;re great to work for.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: John Bolland  Job title: IPS Service Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: ips@cntw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please consider emailing us at ips@cntw.nhs.uk or searching for team members on LinkedIn for further information about the role and first-hand accounts of why we&#39;re great to work for.&lt;/p&gt;
